Marcato Keeps Pressure On IHG After Spurned Deal



        By Zachary Zagger



					Law360, New York (August 4, 2014, 12:38 PM EDT) -- Activist investor Marcato Capital Management LP is again putting pressure on InterContinental Hotels Group PLC to find a merger partner after it turned down a potential deal earlier this year, saying on Monday the timing is right to maximize shareholder value.Marcato, a San Francisco-based investment manager that owns about 4 percent of outstanding shares in IHG, hired global investment bank Houlihan Lokey to assist it in “conducting a full strategic review for enhancing shareholder value at IHG,” the firm said. Still, Marcato said its review...
				
